00:01:08.008 --> 00:01:10.274
So I recommend you have
all that installed.

00:01:10.274 --> 00:01:13.273
Now, the pedestal actually
sits in this groove there.

00:01:13.273 --> 00:01:15.011
Get a tape measure from
the back of the basin

00:01:15.011 --> 00:01:16.658
to the front here and you'll know roughly

00:01:16.658 --> 00:01:18.054
where to seat your pedestal.

00:01:18.054 --> 00:01:19.593
Because really to do this properly

00:01:19.593 --> 00:01:22.275
you need to mock up
the whole installation,

00:01:22.275 --> 00:01:23.108
get a level,

00:01:23.108 --> 00:01:24.639
get your two holes drilled,

00:01:24.639 --> 00:01:26.491
and go from there.

00:01:26.491 --> 00:01:28.297
And then you have to take
it all back down again,

00:01:28.297 --> 00:01:30.551
do your drilling, everything like that

00:01:30.551 --> 00:01:31.676
and put it all back together,

00:01:31.676 --> 00:01:33.249
and get your pipes up where you need them.

00:01:33.249 --> 00:01:35.362
So we'll do that now and let's hope

00:01:35.362 --> 00:01:37.662
